conversation.thought: Nursery_C’s true priority list is ['Parent_B','Parent_A','Parent_D','Parent_E','Parent_C'], so Parent_E is acceptable but ranks below B/A/D. However, by round 28 no higher-priority parent has applied to Nursery_C at all, and Parent_E has repeatedly signaled immediate acceptance and has Nursery_C as first choice, so accepting now secures a feasible match and avoids the risk of remaining unfilled through round 30. Given the late stage and absence of higher-priority applicants in our inbox/history, it is optimal to accept Parent_E.
